[Intro]
[00:10.59] Static in the walls
[00:14.82] Violins rise slowly
[00:20.16] Phone light on the ceiling
[Verse 1]
[00:26.56] I woke up on the flashing sky
[00:30.05] A thousand little miles of light
[00:32.94] They call my name, they sell me dreams
[00:35.48] They follow me into the night
[00:38.78] Inbox open like a wound
[00:40.99] Red numbers climbing in my room
[00:45.06] Everybody needs a piece
[00:46.36] But nobody asks if I can breathe
[Pre-Chorus]
[00:49.50] Scroll by scroll
[00:52.22] I lose the shape of me
[00:56.64] Pin by pin
[00:58.20] I forget what's up
[Chorus]
[01:00.00] What violence means
[01:00.88] I'm looking for a ceasefire in the static
[01:04.94] One quiet place inside the noise
[01:07.60] A little room behind the panic
[01:10.94] Where I can hear my real voice
[01:13.02] I'm looking for a pattern in the madness
[01:16.18] A holy line through broken code
[01:19.45] If peace is somewhere in the chaos
[01:22.14] Then I'm still walking down that road
[01:25.60] Pads in my dreams, ghosts in my feed
[01:28.12] Every open window open
[01:30.00] Something else in me
[01:31.52] Messages stacked like stones
[01:33.26] On a chest that won't let go
[01:34.74] I keep answering the world
[01:36.22] But I don't answer my own soul
[01:37.84] I try to name the storm
[01:39.36] Folders for the pain
[01:40.80] Text for every memory
[01:42.30] Rules for every flame
[01:43.74] But every time I clear the screen
[01:45.54] Another wave comes back
[01:47.10] Another voice
[01:48.04] Another need
[01:48.86] Another signal dressed in black
[01:50.40] Too many tabs
[01:51.18] Too many chains
[01:51.92] Too many faces with borrowed names
[01:53.40] Too many alerts in the bloodstream
[01:54.82] Too many ghosts in the lock screen
[01:56.34] I'm not lost, I'm overloaded
[01:58.08] Heart's still here, just over-coded
[01:59.57] Tryin' to break it
[01:59.98] Read through the interface
[02:01.94] Tryin' to find one sacred space
